{
  "item": {
    "name": "Refresh Token",
    "request": {
      "method": "POST",
      "header": [
        {
          "key": "Accept",
          "value": "application/json"
        },
        {
          "key": "X-Auth-Mode",
          "value": "{{auth_mode}}"
        }
      ],
      "body": {
        "mode": "raw",
        "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}",
        "options": {
          "raw": {
            "language": "json"
          }
        }
      },
      "url": {
        "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/refresh",
        "host": [
          "{{base_url}}"
        ],
        "path": [
          "api",
          "refresh"
        ]
      },
      "description": "Refresh central auth tokens for the authenticated user.\n\n**Auth:** requires authenticated central session/token (`auth:central-api`).\n\n**Query params:** none\n\n**Request body validation:**\n- `refresh_token`: required|string\n  - in cookie mode, this is auto-read from the central refresh cookie if omitted\n\n**Authentication mode:**\nUses `X-Auth-Mode` (`token`|`cookie`).\n- **Token mode:** returns refreshed `access_token` + `refresh_token` + `token_type` + `expires_in` in JSON\n- **Cookie mode:** refreshes HttpOnly cookies and omits token fields from JSON (`expires_in` only)\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Endpoint is rate-limited (`throttle:auth.refresh`)"
    },
    "response": [
      {
        "name": "200 Refreshed (Token Mode)",
        "originalRequest": {
          "method": "POST",
          "header": [],
